                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12719271" author="eribeiro" created="Sun, 14 Jun 2009 14:18:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think so.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hashtable is a legacy class and it&apos;s advised to use Collections.synchronizedMap(new HashMap()) instead. Furthermore, the only reason to use a synchronized Map is concurrency control (it&apos;s the case here?).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 to replace Hashtable for HashMap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12721386" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 18 Jun 2009 18:03:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t find any places Row is used concurrently in multiple threads, so HashMap seems like the Right choice.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Patch also does other minor cleanup to Row-related code that I ran across while looking.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12721446" author="sandeep_tata" created="Thu, 18 Jun 2009 20:11:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Per IRC, we should also clean up misleading comments in Table.load&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12721452" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 18 Jun 2009 20:17:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed w/ comment fix&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12721765" author="hudson" created="Fri, 19 Jun 2009 12:34:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #113 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/113/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/113/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
